cription\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eA package containing all the dependencies to run a single application in isolation.\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eFully virtualized, isolated computers, including all of its hardware and software.\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003c/tr\u003e\n \u003ctr\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eManaged by\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eContainer engines\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eHypervisors\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003c/tr\u003e\n \u003ctr\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eUse cases\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eDeploy applications in cloud-native environments, quickly scale service capacity, improve application portability.\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eRunning Legacy applications, consolidating servers, developing software on an isolated operating system environment.\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003c/tr\u003e\n \u003ctr\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eNotable examples\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eDocker, Amazon ECS, Red Hat Openshift.\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003ctd\u003eVMWare Fusion, Oracle VirtualBox, Microsoft Hyper-V.\u003c/td\u003e\n \u003c/tr\u003e\n \u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"containers-can-rsquo-t-run-full-operating-systems\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e5 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Containers can’t run full operating systems\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"containers-are-designed-for-single-applications\"\u003e\n            Containers are designed for single applications\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;Hypervisors like Hyper-V let you run fully-fledged operating systems on a single host.\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2103\" height=\"1196\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A screenshot of a windows 11 VM running in Hyper-V\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-virtual-machine.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003eHypervisors like Hyper-V let you run fully-fledged operating systems on a single host.\u003c/p\u003e\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Virtual machines run on top of a hypervisor, which in turn runs on the host operating system. They are great for any situation requiring multiple operating systems on the same machine. With them, you can run any number of Linux distributions or Windows versions concurrently, provided you have the hardware to power them all.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eVirtual machines are excellent for running OS-specific programs, such as proprietary software or legacy applications. They’re also ideal for situations requiring stronger isolation and security.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eContainers, on the other hand, run on a container engine over the host operating system, but they are designed to run only a specific application. Container installation packages, called images, include only the application and its required files. All containers share the same host operating system.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"containers-are-leaner\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e4 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Containers are leaner\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"containers-use-less-resource\"\u003e\n            Containers use less resource\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;Docker is the big name in container solutions.\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1736\" height=\"1117\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A screenshot of a docker container log\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-screenshot.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003eDocker is the big name in container solutions.\u003c/p\u003e\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Because containers do not run operating systems, they are much leaner and consume fewer resources than virtual machines. This makes them ideal for running multiple containers simultaneously, as developer teams often do.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSetting up and sharing containers is also easy. Once an application has been packaged into a container image, you can easily move it between machines or share it on a platform like GitHub. Docker, a popular container platform, has its Docker Registry container distributor built into its desktop client.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"containers-are-quicker-to-set-up\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Containers are quicker to set up\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"containers-are-faster-to-spin-up-and-shut-down\"\u003e\n            Containers are faster to spin up and shut down\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;If you have an image file ready, you can fire up a container in seconds. The Docker Registry (above) also lets you download pre-packaged images from its library.\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1697\" height=\"1115\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A screenshot of the Docker Registry\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-docker-registry-screenshot.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003eIf you have an image file ready, you can fire up a container in seconds. The Docker Registry (above) also lets you download pre-packaged images from its library.\u003c/p\u003e\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e To set up an application within a virtual machine, you’ll need to allocate its resources, install the operating system, and set up all the files the application needs. Conversely, setting up a container’s pre-packaged image file takes just a couple of clicks or commands.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eA container’s speedy installation time makes it useful in many situations. For example, in cloud applications that need scalability, a load balancer can instantly spin up container instances to handle an unexpected workload spike or shut them down on demand to save resources.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"virtual-machines-have-greater-isolation\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Virtual machines have greater isolation\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"virtual-machines-are-better-for-security\"\u003e\n            Virtual machines are better for security\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1386\" height=\"825\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A screenshot of Microsoft Hyper-V\u0026#39;s security options panel\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-security-options-setting-1.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Virtual machines (and their hypervisors) virtualize the entire hardware stack, including processors, memory, storage, and even network adapters. Since they run their own operating system, they also encapsulate their own kernel and software stack. This setup creates a strong isolation between the host operating system and between virtual machines.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eContainers also provide isolation between each other, but since they share all hardware resources and run on a single host operating system, their isolation is less robust.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eTo get the best of both worlds, containers are often run inside virtual machines.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"virtual-machines-are-more-complex\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e1 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Virtual machines are more complex\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"they-can-be-easily-customized-for-specific-needs\"\u003e\n            They can be easily customized for specific needs\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;You can customize the virtualized hardware resources for a VM.\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"1692\" height=\"1137\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A screenshot of the Hyper-V VM editor\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/xda-hyper-v-vm-customization-1.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003eYou can customize the virtualized hardware resources for a VM.\u003c/p\u003e\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Since they virtualize both hardware and software, virtual machines are suitable for complex setups. Within them, you can create a completely separate development environment or workspace, something containers aren\u0026#39;t designed for. Unlike virtual machines, most container applications are managed via commands rather than a graphical interface. While graphical interfaces are supported, they are not commonly used, as those who work with containers are typically seasoned developers.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"containers-and-virtual-machines-are-similar-in-concept-but-are-worlds-apart\"\u003e\n            Containers and virtual machines are similar in concept but are worlds apart\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are many ways virtual machines and containers are used in development, but their similarities can be a little confusing. In a nutshell, containers are isolated instances of applications, while virtual machines are virtualized full computers. The former is quick to deploy, while the latter is better suited for complex tasks. Neither replaces the other; they are often used in tandem in cloud applications, servers and database management, and software development.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"b04f-4d54-bdc857c26a9e\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-docker-containers-for-developers/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/best-docker-containers-for-developers.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                